don't%20want%20to%20offend%2045%25%20of%20the%20population%26quot%3B%20by%20visibly%20backing%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20remains%20unclear%20whether%20Trump's%20legal%20team%20was%20aware%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-pleads-poverty-new-york-civil-fraud-trial-bond-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enegotiations%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20Hankey%20and%20Trump's%20representatives%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20post%20the%20full%20%24464%20million%20amount%2C%20which%20was%20underway%20when%20the%20bond%20was%20reduced.%20However%2C%20legal%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20that%20if%20his%20lawyers%20knew%20about%20the%20offer%20and%20failed%20to%20notify%20the%20court%2C%20they%20may%20have%20violated%20ethics%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20outlet%20contacted%20Trump's%20representatives%2C%20Hankey%20reached%20back%20out%20to%20ProPublica.%20In%20the%20second%20conversation%2C%20he%20told%20ProPublica%20that%20accepting%20Trump's%20real%20estate%20as%20collateral%20would%20have%20been%20complicated%2C%20and%20the%20deal%20would%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bdifficult.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20happens%20now%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20New%20York%20State%20Bar%20Association%2C%20attorneys%20are%20bound%20to%20the%20NY%20Rules%20of%20Professional%20Conduct%2C%20as%20adopted%20by%20the%20Appellate%20Division%20of%20the%20State%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAttorneys%20who%20violate%20the%20law%20or%20fail%20to%20abide%20by%20this%20code%20of%20conduct%20are%20subject%20to%20discipline%2C%20which%20may%20include%20admonishment%2C%20reprimand%2C%20censure%2C%20suspension%20or%20loss%20of%20his%20or%20her%20license%20to%20practice%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnysba.org%2Fpublic-resources%2Fguide-to-attorney-discipline%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENYSBA%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20legal%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20if%20Trump's%20attorneys%20knew%20of%20the%20negotiations%20surrounding%20Hankey's%20offer%20as%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-bond-reduction-civil-fraud-case-rare-legal-experts-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappealed%20to%20the%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20lower%20bond%20amount%2C%20it%20would%20likely%20be%20an%20ethics%20violation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Trump's%20lawyers%20knew%20it%20was%20possible%20for%20him%20to%20secure%20a%20bond%20for%20the%20full%20amount%20when%20they%20filed%20their%20appeal%2C%20then%20their%20misrepresentation%20may%20be%20an%20ethics%20violation%20and%20a%20fraud%20on%20the%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20Neama%20Rahmani%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20However%2C%20he%20noted%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20prove%20what%20Trump's%20lawyers%20knew%20and%20when%20they%20knew%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lieb%2C%20a%20litigation%20attorney%20and%20legal%20analyst%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Econduct%20of%20Trump's%20attorneys%20in%20this%20matter%20appears%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20clear%20violation%26quot%3B%20of%20rule%203.3%20of%20the%20NY%20Rules%20of%20Professional%20Conduct%2C%20which%20states%20lawyers%20shall%20not%20knowingly%20make%20false%20statements%20of%20fact%20to%20the%20court%20and%20that%20they%20shall%20make%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20remedial%20measures%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20disclosure%20to%20the%20court%20if%20they%20come%20to%20know%20of%20a%20falsehood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShould%20Trump's%20lawyers%20be%20found%20to%20violate%20this%20rule%2C%20they%20should%20expect%20an%20ethics%20charge%20be%20levied%20against%20them%2C%20which%20can%20result%20in%20anything%20from%20a%20private%20letter%20in%20their%20file%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%20a%20suspension%20from%20practice%2C%26quot%3B%20Lieb%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%