F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20chief%20technology%20officer%2C%20Mira%20Murati%2C%20said%20she%20doesn't%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DmAUpxN-EIgU%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%2C%20Murati%20was%20asked%20if%20OpenAI's%20text-to-video%20generator%20Sora%20was%20trained%20on%20video%20content%20from%20YouTube.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20actually%20not%20sure%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Murati%20told%20the%20Journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube's%20CEO%20Neal%20Mohan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-04-04%2Fyoutube-says-openai-training-sora-with-its-videos-would-break-the-rules%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday%20that%20he%20also%20does%20not%20know%20if%20OpenAI%20is%20using%20YouTube%20content%20to%20train%20its%20video%20generator.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Sora%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20using%20YouTube%20content%2C%20that%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bclear%20violation%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20platform's%20terms%20of%20service%2C%20Mohan%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20creator's%20perspective%2C%20when%20a%20creator%20uploads%20their%20hard%20work%20to%20our%20platform%2C%20they%20have%20certain%20expectations%2C%26quot%3B%20Mohan%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etold%20Bloomberg's%20Emily%20Chang.%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20those%20expectations%20is%20that%20the%20terms%20of%20service%20is%20going%20to%20be%20abided%20by.%20It%20does%20not%20allow%20for%20things%20like%20transcripts%20or%20video%20bits%20to%20be%20downloaded%2C%20and%20that%20is%20a%20clear%20violation%20of%20our%20terms%20of%20service.%20Those%20are%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20road%20in%20terms%20of%20content%20on%20our%20platform.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMohan%20added%20that%20Google%20(which%20owns%20YouTube)%20does%20use%20some%20YouTube%20videos%20t