20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20products%20and%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20you%20make%20smart%20decisions%20with%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jam%20Lam%20freelance%20writer%20selfie%20in%20front%20of%20red%20truck%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6531905a96908fd7cdb3161a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Jackie%20Lam.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jackie%20Lam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEarthquake%20insurance%20comes%20with%20a%20deductible%20based%20on%20the%20value%20of%20your%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhile%20FEMA%20provides%20help%20in%20some%20disasters%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20replacement%20for%20earthquake%20insurance.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBecause%20of%20the%20potentially%20high%20deductible%2C%20earthquake%20insurance%20isn't%20right%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20ago%20I%20was%20helping%20my%20mom%20revisit%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-homeowners-insurance-companies%5C%22%3Ehomeowners%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20see%20if%20she%20should%20add%20an%20earthquake%20insurance%20policy.%20And%20to%20be%20blunt%2C%20I%20found%20it%20all%20very%20confusing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20unsure%20about%20how%20the%20deductible%20worked%2C%20and%20my%20mom%20said%20that%20many%20relatives%20and%20friends%20decided%20against%20it%20because%20FEMA%20supposedly%20could%20provide%20assistance%20should%20an%20earthquake%20strike.%20So%20I%20reached%20out%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fseok-dahl-729a86b0%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESeok%20Dahl%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20insurance%20agent%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffarmers-homeowners-insurance-review%5C%22%3EFarmers%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20is%20based%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20to%20answer%20some%20of%20my%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDahl%20explains%20that%20homeowners%20insurance%20and%20earthquake%20insurance%20are%20two%20completely%20different%20policies.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20comparing%20apples%20to%20oranges.%20Even%20though%20they're%20about%20your%20property%2C%20earthquake%20insurance%20only%20covers%20property%20from%20ground%20movement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20I%20learned%20about%20getting%20earthquake%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Your%20deductible%20is%20based%20on%20the%20current%20value%20of%20the%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20homeowners%20insurance%2C%20where%20it's%20a%20set%20dollar%20amount%20that%20you%20pick%2C%20and%20is%20usually%20anywhere%20from%20%24500%20to%20%241%2C000%2C%20your%20earthquake%20deductible%20is%20a%20percentage%20of%20the%20current%20value%20of%20your%20home.%20So%20if%20your%20home%20is%20valued%20at%20%24500%2C000%2C%20and%20the%20deductible%20is%2010%25%2C%20then%20you%20need%20to%20pay%20%2450%2C000%20before%20insurance%20kicks%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20an%20earthquake%20deductible%20is%20usually%20anywhere%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iii.org%2Farticle%2Funderstanding-your-insurance-deductibles%5C%22%3E2%25%20to%2020%25%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20states%20where%20there's%20a%20greater%20likelihood%20of%20an%20earthquake%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20turn%20a%20higher%20risk%20%E2%80%94%20the%20deductible%20starts%20at%20a%20higher%20percentage.%20The%20California%20Earthquake%20Authority%2C%20which%20provides%20most%20of%20the%20earthquake%20insurance%20policies%20where%20I%20live%2C%20has%20deductibles%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insurance.ca.gov%2F01-consumers%2F105-type%2F95-guides%2F03-res%2Feq-ins.cfm%5C%22%3Estarting%20at%205%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20jaw%20dropped%20when%20I%20figured%20this%20out%2C%20and%20I%20asked%20my%20mom's%20insurance%20agent%20several%20times%20if%20this%20was%20indeed%20correct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Your%20earthquake%20dwelling%20insurance%20cannot%20be%20less%20than%20your%20homeowners%20dwelling%20insurance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Dahl%20explains%2C%20the%20dwelling%20portion%20coverage%20of%20your%20earthquake%20insurance%20has%20to%20match%20or%20be%20higher%20than%20the%20dwelling%20portion%20coverage%20of%20your%20homeowners%20insurance.%20So%20if%20your%20home%20is%20insured%20for%20%24500%2C000%20under%20your%20earthquake%20insurance%20policy%2C%20it%20should%20also%20be%20insured%20for%20%24500%2C000%20for%20your%20homeowners%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20homeowners%20insurance%2C%20the%20three%20main%20types%20of%20coverage%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDwelling%20coverage.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-dwelling-coverage%5C%22%3EDwelling%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20pay%20to%20rebuild%20your%20home%20to%20its%20current%20value.%20It%20doesn't%20include%20contents%20or%20land%2C%20but%20it%20does%20include%20fixtures%20and%20permanent%20appliances.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EContents%20coverage.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Contents%20coverage%20will%20pay%20to%20replace%20or%20repair%20your%20belongings%2C%20such%20as%20furniture%2C%20clothing%2C%20electronics%2C%20and%20appliances.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ELoss%20of%20use.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Should%20you%20need%20to%20temporarily%20uproot%20because%20of%20damage%20to%20your%20home%20from%20an%20earthquake%2C%20loss%20of%20use%20coverage%20can%20pay%20for%20the%20cost%20of%20accommodations%2C%20meals%2C%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20any%20loss%20of%20wages.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Earthquake%20insurance%20includes%20some%20exceptions%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20earthquake%20insurance%20technically%20includes%20most%20damage%20and%20destruction%20to%20your%20home%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20ground%20tremor%2C%20there%20are%20some%20exceptions%2C%20such%20as%20a%20fire.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20fire%20arises%20from%20that%20earthquake%2C%20maybe%20from%20the%20eruption%20of%20a%20gas%20line%2C%20that's%20not%20covered%20under%20your%20earthquake%20insurance%2C%20but%20from%20under%20your%20home%20insurance%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dahl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDamage%20to%20your%20vehicle%20is%20also%20not%20usually%20covered%2C%20and%20you%20would%20need%20to%20purchase%20a%20separate%20policy%20should%20there%20be%20flooding.%20Last%2C%20any%20damage%20to%20your%20land%20%E2%80%94%20think%20sinkholes%2C%20landslides%20and%20erosion%20%E2%80%94%20isn't%20covered%20by%20earthquake%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20FEMA%20only%20offers%20assistance%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20president-mandated%20order%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EContrary%20to%20what%20one%20might%20believe%2C%20FEMA%20is%20not%20an%20insurance%20policy%2C%20says%20Dahl.%20In%20turn%2C%20FEMA%20cannot%20replace%20your%20insurance%20policy.%20FEMA%20only%20steps%20in%20when%20there's%20a%20catastrophic%20disaster.%20So%20if%20there%20was%20a%20minor%20shake%20but%20your%20home%20suffered%20damage%2C%20you%20can't%20call%20on%20FEMA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20might%20think%20that%20the%20government%20is%20stepping%20in%20to%20rescue%20you%20for%20your%20damage%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20has%20to%20be%20a%20catastrophic%20event%20that's%20severe%20enough%20for%20the%20governor%20to%20request%20the%20federal%20government%20to%20step%20in%20to%20help%20the%20state.%20And%20only%20the%20president%20has%20the%20right%20to%20execute%20that%20order.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fema.gov%2Ffact-sheet%2Fhazard-mitigation-under-individuals-and-households-program%5C%22%3Emaximum%20amount%20of%20assistance%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20FEMA%20can%20offer%20per%20household%2C%20and%20that's%20%2436%2C000.%20That%20being%20said%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommunity.fema.gov%2FPreparednessConnect%2Fs%2Farticle%2FMyths-vs-Facts-The-True-Cost-of-Flooding%5C%22%3Eaverage%20amount%20FEMA%20pays%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20%245%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Earthquake%20insurance%20may%20or%20not%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20you%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Dahl%20obviously%20thinks%20it%20is%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20have%20earthquake%20insurance%2C%20it's%20expensive%20coverage%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20largely%20a%20personal%20decision.%20To%20help%20you%20gauge%20whether%20it's%20a%20good%20choice%20for%20your%20needs%2C%20Dahl%20recommends%20considering%20factors%20such%20as%20your%20personality%2C%20lifestyle%2C%20and%20your%20asset%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20a%20fire%2C%20earthquake%20insurance%20can%20cover%20a%20severe%20or%20minor%20event%2C%20explains%20Dahl.%20Think%20about%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20getting%20earthquake%20insurance.%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20want%20to%20ask%20yourself%2C%20'Do%20I%20want%20to%20pay%20this%20earthquake%20insurance%20for%20the%20protection%20of%20my%20house%3F'%20If%20you%20can't%20afford%20to%20pay%20for%20earthquake%20insurance%2C%20then%2C%20you%20shouldn't.%20That's%20because%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20end%20up%20canceling%20it%20anyway.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20because%20there's%20such%20a%20high%20deductible%20on%20earthquake%20insurance%2C%20it%20only%20really%20comes%20in%20handy%20during%20a%20catastrophe.%20But%20if%20much%20of%20your%20assets%20are%20tied%20into%20a%20home%2C%20it%20also%20might%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20get%20earthquake%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%2C%20if%20you're%20the%20type%20of%20person%20who%20is%20going%20to%20sit%20and%20worry%20all%20the%20time%2C%20it%20might%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20purchase%20earthquake%20insurance%2C%20says%20Dahl.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20choice%20is%20yours.%20I'm%20a%20worrywart%2C%20and%20I'd%20rather%20spend%20that%20extra%20money%20each%20year%20and%20have%20peace%20of%20mind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasked-financial-planner-about-getting-earthquake-insurance-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712355062000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6610644216bde8d4ead6488c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasked-financial-planner-about-getting-earthquake-insurance-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Earthquake%20insurance%20comes%20with%20a%20high%20deductible%2C%20so%20it%20may%20not%20be%20worth%20it%20for%20everyone%2C%20but%20if%20you%20can%20afford%20it%2C%20it%20can%20be%20valuable.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jackie%20Lam)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasked-financial-planner-about-getting-earthquake-insurance-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NY%20police%20to%20pay%20%2417.5m%20over%20hijab%20mugshot%20row%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712353879000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F1143%2Fproduction%2F_133091440_gettyimages-641792872.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68746628%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20lawsuit%20was%20brought%20by%20two%20women%20who%20were%20forced%20to%20remove%20head%20coverings%20to%20be%20photographed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A54%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworl